column5: At the Narrows here in Orillia these guys make a stopover for a couple weeks and then take off up north I see them every year and I got some pic this time.  I see a few goldeneyes and maybe a few mergansers.
Yep I seen 4 geese yesturday fly by.It coming,yes it,s a coming.
Looks like the ice will be gone for the Perch Festival. Nice pictures Matt.

BAM, BAM, BAM!!!, oops, season is not open, mmmmmmmmmmmmmmm......goldeneyes.  Actually, have quit hunting waterfowl, many years ago, just not enough time in my life to partake of them any more, sold all my decoys.
